Disease:     Hepatitis B
Type:        Viral
Pathogen:    HBV
Transmission:Blood, sexual contact
Symptoms:    Often asymptomatic; jaundice
Treatment:   Antivirals (tenofovir)
Deaths/yr:   0.82M
Vaccine:     Yes (highly effective)
Discovered:  1965

Disease:     Cancer
Type:        Cellular
Pathogen:    Various causes
Transmission:Non-communicable
Symptoms:    Lumps, weight loss, fatigue
Treatment:   Chemo, surgery, immunotherapy
Deaths/yr:   10.0M
Vaccine:     Some (HPV, Hep B vaccines)
Discovered:  Ancient

Disease:     Alzheimer's
Type:        Neurological
Pathogen:    Non-communicable
Transmission:Aging/genetics
Symptoms:    Memory loss, confusion
Treatment:   No cure; slowing medications
Deaths/yr:   0.12M
Vaccine:     No
Discovered:  1906

